<td width=50%><font color=white>Posted By: Hueydini</font></td><td width=50% align=right><font color=white>2000-07-27 12:14:31</font></td></tr><tr>
<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>The lens is not no-drop. When you get it, just go to the Windmills and head straight north, you'll see a couple huts with one of them having an enchanter pet pacing around it, that's the one.  She sees me amiably and I completed the quest twice.  She would not allow my wood-elf ranger companion to do it, however. I used my lvl 29 cleric and my partner's 33 ranger to get the lens and if I were not full mana we wouldn't have succeeded. This room is very difficult for casters since they have difficulty medding because of the seemingly continual passing by of green mobs which will interrupt your medding and the necessity to root every one of them so that they don't bring back the whole dungeon.  Good luck.  </font></td></tr></table>
